The paper discusses the use of neural networks for approximate reasoning in a fixed dimensional latent space, which is a common topic in the fields of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The use of embeddings and vector spaces is also a common technique in natural language processing (cs.CL) and computer vision (cs.CV). Finally, the use of graph neural networks is a specific technique within the field of neural networks (cs.NE).
